cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a machine learning approach to extract socioeconomic indicators from high-resolution satellite imagery, which involves using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and transfer learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as transfer learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence to extract insights from unstructured data, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also deals with remote sensing data, which could place it in the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of data to inform policy decisions, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
